<!-- WORK -->
<section id=3D"work">
  <div class=3D"section-inner">
    <p class=3D"section-eyebrow">Experience</p>
    <h2 class=3D"section-title">Work that moved the business</h2>
    <div class=3D"work-cards">

      <div class=3D"work-card">
        <div class=3D"card-meta">
          <span class=3D"card-tag">Strategy and Revenue</span>
          <span class=3D"card-company">S&amp;P Global (via IHS Markit merge=
r)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class=3D"card-title">Turned fragmented benchmark workflows into=
 a $1M+ ARR subscription product</h3>
        <p class=3D"card-body">Investment managers were manually matching f=
und strategies to static PDF benchmarks outside the platform =E2=80=94 a br=
ittle two-step process that eroded trust in performance data. Led the strat=
egic case for embedding Cambridge Associates benchmark data directly into i=
Level by strategy, currency, and methodology. Defined the integration archi=
tecture, drove partner selection over a competing Preqin bid, and launched =
a subscription-based in-platform analytics product with audit controls. S&a=
mp;P now manages quarterly distribution; CA handles granular regional calcu=
lations across APAC, North America, and Europe.</p>
        <div class=3D"card-outcomes">
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">$1M+ incremental ARR</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Competitive analysis: CA vs Preqin</=
span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Product-led revenue model</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Subscription launch</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class=3D"work-card">
        <div class=3D"card-meta">
          <span class=3D"card-tag">Platform Reliability</span>
          <span class=3D"card-company">S&amp;P Global (via IHS Markit merge=
r)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class=3D"card-title">Led platform migration from monolith to mi=
croservices, cutting incidents by 80%</h3>
        <p class=3D"card-body">A monolithic platform architecture was gener=
ating 10 SEV1/SEV2 incidents per six months across 700 institutional client=
s. Partnered with architecture and engineering leads to define the migratio=
n strategy from monolithic workflows to a microservices-based platform, mak=
ing trade-off decisions across scalability, latency targets, and rollback r=
isk. Owned the product requirements and acceptance criteria through every s=
print. Delivered 99.95% SLO and reduced critical incidents to 2 per six mon=
ths =E2=80=94 directly protecting renewal conversations across BlackRock, H=
amilton Lane, and AIA.</p>
        <div class=3D"card-outcomes">
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">99.95% SLO</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">SEV1/SEV2 reduced 10 to 2</span=
>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Architecture trade-off leadership</s=
pan>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Cross-team delivery</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class=3D"work-card">
        <div class=3D"card-meta">
          <span class=3D"card-tag">AI and Analytics</span>
          <span class=3D"card-company">S&amp;P Global (via IHS Markit merge=
r)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class=3D"card-title">Delivered 83% accuracy on natural-language=
 portfolio queries for 300+ enterprise users using a fine-tuned in-house LL=
M</h3>
        <p class=3D"card-body">Investment teams needed natural-language acc=
ess to portfolio data, but deploying a frontier LLM off-the-shelf posed reg=
ulatory language and institutional tone risks. Made the strategic decision =
to integrate Spark Assist =E2=80=94 a fine-tuned in-house LLM trained on S&=
amp;P tone, behavior, and proprietary financial knowledge =E2=80=94 rather =
than use a frontier model, achieving significant cost advantage and domain =
precision. Defined the production-readiness evaluation framework with real =
query test cases from SMEs and friendly clients, synthetic red-team dataset=
s, and behavioral guardrails. Implemented authorization-before-retrieval ar=
chitecture to enforce access control at the retrieval layer before any LLM =
call.</p>
        <div class=3D"card-outcomes">
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">83% accuracy</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">300+ enterprise users</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Fine-tuned in-house LLM</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Enterprise compliance architecture</=
span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class=3D"work-card">
        <div class=3D"card-meta">
          <span class=3D"card-tag">Compliance and Security</span>
          <span class=3D"card-company">S&amp;P Global (via IHS Markit merge=
r)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class=3D"card-title">Blocked a multi-product rollout to protect=
 100% GDPR compliance across EU clients</h3>
        <p class=3D"card-body">A planned unified suite rollout was viable i=
n the US but would have violated GDPR data residency requirements for EU cl=
ients by co-mingling US and EU data on shared infrastructure. Authored the =
trade-off decision document and RAID log escalated to executive leadership,=
 making the case to halt the rollout until regional server separation was i=
mplemented. Defined the architectural requirements for US/EU separation, wo=
rked with engineering to confirm compliance across all EU client data, and =
established the governance gate before any further platform investment was =
approved.</p>
        <div class=3D"card-outcomes">
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill gold">100% GDPR compliance</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Executive decision document</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Risk escalation leadership</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Regional architecture definition</sp=
an>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class=3D"work-card">
        <div class=3D"card-meta">
          <span class=3D"card-tag">Voice of Customer</span>
          <span class=3D"card-company">S&amp;P Global (via IHS Markit merge=
r)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class=3D"card-title">Built a multi-channel VOC system that fed =
every roadmap decision for 700 institutional clients</h3>
        <p class=3D"card-body">Roadmap prioritization across two concurrent=
 products (iLevel and iPreo Prism) required synthesizing signal from client=
s managing trillions in AUM. Built and operated a structured VOC system com=
bining Pendo behavioral analytics, quarterly NPS surveys, Aha feedback, acc=
ount management escalations, and direct discovery sessions with GPs, LPs, a=
nd CPOs at BlackRock, Hamilton Lane, and AIA. Translated multi-source insig=
ht into 6 to 12 month roadmaps prioritized by client impact, severity, and =
business alignment, presented to executive leadership each cycle.</p>
        <div class=3D"card-outcomes">
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Pendo and Aha analytics</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Direct CPO discovery sessions</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Two-product roadmap ownership</span>
          <span class=3D"outcome-pill">Executive roadmap presentation</span=
>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

